1
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:59,640
Because of that damn ghost,
everyone thinks I'm crazy.

2
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:02,559
Because I can't contact anyone else.

3
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:04,439
I need your help.

4
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,760
You have to help me!

5
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:13,920
<i>I have a job for you.
Find Sarai's family treasure.</i>

6
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,640
Keep this with you.

7
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:21,000
That woman's spirit
won't be able to come near you.

8
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:24,920
I'm interested
in the plot of land next to yours.

9
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:10,000
I'm scared!

10
00:04:14,920 --> 00:04:16,200
Please help me.

11
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,879
Please don't be scared of me.

12
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,079
I'm scared. I'm scared.

13
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:37,440
No. No. Stay away!

14
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,720
Hey. Sir.

15
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,200
Sir.

16
00:05:13,960 --> 00:05:14,800
Sir.

17
00:05:16,040 --> 00:05:17,080
Sir!

18
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:27,400
Sir. Sir.

19
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,680
Sir.

20
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,640
Are you alright?

21
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,999
It's here.

22
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,320
- What?
- It's here.

23
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,799
Sir. Sir.

24
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,919
Look ahead. Look ahead.

25
00:05:48,920 --> 00:05:52,599
Don't turn around.
The moment you turn around, you die.

26
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:54,320
Don't turn around.

27
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,360
Why are you suddenly
interested in Sompong?

28
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:21,159
He says strange things all the time,

29
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,479
like he's terrified of something.

30
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,639
GENEROSITY, VIRTUE, MEDITATION,
WISDOM, AND PERFECTION

31
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,480
I just want to know why he lost his mind.

32
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,480
You've been here a long time,

33
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,080
so I thought you might know something.

34
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:41,080
Everything comes from karma.

35
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:45,560
Sompong is simply receiving
the consequences

36
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,880
of what he has done.

37
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,560
And...

38
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:55,240
Oh, you came to make merit too?

39
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,960
I just stopped by to talk with him.

40
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:02,200
Are you here to offer alms?

41
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:07,040
- Let me offer these first.
- Of course.

42
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:18,119
Some of us

43
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:21,799
try our hardest to preserve nature.

44
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,159
But other people

45
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:26,040
only think about exploiting it for profit.

46
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:28,600
It's awful.

47
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:33,239
Yesterday,

48
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,720
someone came wanting to buy
the land next to my house.

49
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:39,880
He probably saw the scenery around there
and figured it could make money.

50
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:45,199
I don't think he only wants
the land beside your house.

51
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:48,359
He probably wants your property too,

52
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,880
since it's all one connected plot.

53
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,119
That's what I thought.

54
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:54,400
So I rejected him immediately.

55
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:57,160
Actually, Mr. Narathon,

56
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:00,879
I talked with my wife
about the aquarium project,

57
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:04,760
she said it might be too ambitious.

58
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,799
So I'd like

59
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,039
to offer the land beside my house

60
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:11,440
to you to expand
your rare marine breeding project.

61
00:08:13,120 --> 00:08:14,119
Really?

62
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:15,560
Of course.

63
00:08:16,640 --> 00:08:20,480
I think your current place
feels too cramped anyway.

64
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,200
Are you interested?

65
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,440
Of course.

66
00:08:24,960 --> 00:08:26,319
I'm very interested.

67
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:30,039
Actually, I've wanted to expand too,

68
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:33,640
but like you said,
my current place is too small.

69
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,240
Then let's work on this project together.

70
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,760
Of course.

71
00:08:57,480 --> 00:09:01,320
It smells amazing, Mom.
Looks delicious too.

72
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,760
That good?

73
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,319
Let me help serve it.

74
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:07,719
It's alright.

75
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:11,599
Dad should be back from the temple soon.
Are you hungry?

76
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,639
It's alright.
I'd rather wait for Dad and eat together.

77
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:15,760
Alright.

78
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,720
Who could that be this early?

79
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,159
I'll check, Mom.

80
00:09:35,160 --> 00:09:36,400
Okay.

81
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:45,320
Mr. Phum.

82
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,560
It's you.

83
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,120
You live here?

84
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,520
Yes. This is my parents' house.

85
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,319
Oh, it's you.

86
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:59,880
Hello.

87
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:03,240
Mom, you know Mr. Phum too?

88
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:10,719
I never imagined

89
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:14,280
you were the one who bought
all of Mook's photographs.

90
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:15,960
Thank you so much.

91
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:18,919
No need to thank me.

92
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:21,839
Kaimook's work has value

93
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,359
because she devoted herself to it,
diving deep beneath the sea.

94
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:26,319
Not everyone can do that.

95
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:29,039
And once I learned
she planned to use the money

96
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:31,119
to support marine conservation,

97
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,719
I wanted to support her even more.

98
00:10:32,720 --> 00:10:36,040
Nature can't survive
unless we work together to protect it.

99
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:40,279
I wish her father could hear that.

100
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,240
Then he wouldn't misunderstand you.

101
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,680
Why, Mom?

102
00:10:45,560 --> 00:10:47,839
Mr. Phum came wanting
to buy the land beside our house.

103
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:51,920
Your father was worried he might use it
for something harmful to nature.

104
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:58,240
Dad is very against
environmental destruction.

105
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:01,000
So what do you want
the land for, Mr. Phum?

106
00:11:01,720 --> 00:11:04,359
I want to build an eco-resort.

107
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,199
A place that encourages tourists

108
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:09,120
to respect nature and the environment.

109
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,920
That sounds interesting.

110
00:11:13,040 --> 00:11:16,680
Then perhaps you could help
speak to your father for me.

111
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:20,839
I doubt that'll work.

112
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,760
No matter what,
I'm not selling you that land.

113
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,799
I hope

114
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,199
you'll reconsider carefully.

115
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:37,400
I have a very attractive offer.

116
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,560
Really?

117
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,879
Well unfortunately, I've already decided

118
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:47,040
to work with Mr. Narathon
on a rare marine breeding project.

119
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,520
Mr. Narathon

120
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,400
is exactly the kind of young man

121
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:57,840
society should admire.

122
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:00,640
Is that so?

123
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,999
Yes. Because he only wants

124
00:12:04,000 --> 00:12:07,120
to preserve nature and the environment.

125
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:11,280
He doesn't think
only about profit and destruction,

126
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,280
unlike some people.

127
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:24,720
Well, Mr. Narathon, please have a seat.

128
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:30,240
You're certainly persistent,
Mr. Phum, coming here this early.

129
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:33,879
I live by one principle.
Where there's a will,

130
00:12:33,880 --> 00:12:35,960
there's a way.

131
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,480
Then perhaps
you should find a new principle.

132
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:41,280
Because it won't work.

133
00:12:42,920 --> 00:12:46,640
It's alright.
As much as I regret losing this land,

134
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,199
at least you trust Narathon enough

135
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,199
to let him work on the project he loves.

136
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,199
Expanding his rare marine breeding project

137
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:56,000
has always been his dream.

138
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:59,840
I don't get it, but my son gets it.
That isn't such a bad balance after all.

139
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:04,359
Wait, you didn't know?

140
00:13:04,360 --> 00:13:06,519
Narathon is my son.

141
00:13:06,520 --> 00:13:08,080
My only son, actually.

142
00:13:25,640 --> 00:13:27,160
Are you satisfied now, Dad?

143
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:31,920
What did I do?

144
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:36,439
Trying to make Mr. Mek know
that you're my father.

145
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:38,120
Am I not your father?

146
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,520
You know how I feel about you.

147
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:46,120
I never even wanted anyone
to know I'm your son.

148
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:51,000
Yes.

149
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:54,759
I know you don't accept
or respect me as your father.

150
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:57,839
Honestly, I don't want to force you
to feel anything.

151
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:59,880
Unfortunately, I can't resign
from being your father.

152
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,400
Should I apologize to you too?

153
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,919
For bringing you into this world,

154
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,159
raising you well,

155
00:14:07,160 --> 00:14:10,600
until you're now telling me that you
don't want anyone to know I'm your father?

156
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:13,479
Take good care of your project.

157
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:15,760
The moment you fail,
I'll come back and take this land.

158
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,480
No matter what,

159
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:30,960
money still matters to you
more than people's feelings.

160
00:14:36,280 --> 00:14:37,560
Mr. Thon,

161
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,000
there's something I want to ask you.

162
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,360
No matter what obstacles I face,

163
00:15:20,320 --> 00:15:23,200
I will make that land mine.

164
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:42,120
Why do you want my land so badly?

165
00:15:44,280 --> 00:15:45,680
Is it because of this place?

166
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,200
Is that why you sent people to kill me?

167
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:54,680
You killed me, didn't you? Mr. Phum!

168
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:32,200
You probably want to ask why I didn't
tell you he was my father

169
00:16:32,800 --> 00:16:35,360
when I saw him earlier, right?

170
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:39,799
Why would you need to tell me?
I don't care

171
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:43,280
whose son you are or who your father is.

172
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,600
You said you had something to ask me.

173
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:53,720
I wanted to ask about
the curse of Skull Island.

174
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,120
You still haven't told me about it.

175
00:16:57,880 --> 00:16:59,320
But it's a long story.

176
00:17:00,920 --> 00:17:02,160
It's mysterious,

177
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,358
terrifying, thrilling, and scary.

178
00:17:05,359 --> 00:17:06,680
Enough.

179
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,559
Even if it's horrifying enough
to make my hair stand on end,

180
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,760
I'll listen.

181
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:14,160
You're not scared?

182
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:17,880
I'm not scared. Will you tell me now?

183
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:21,440
Not yet.

184
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:24,400
You can't hear

185
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:28,400
a story like this just anywhere.
You think I'll tell it for free?

186
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:33,000
I haven't eaten anything
since this morning.

187
00:17:33,680 --> 00:17:36,400
If I told it while we ate,

188
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:39,360
it would be much more enjoyable.

189
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:59,760
Are you planning the fish breeding farm?

190
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:03,480
Are you going to start right away?

191
00:18:06,080 --> 00:18:09,679
I'm thinking of
putting this project on hold for now.

192
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:12,920
What? Why?

193
00:18:14,880 --> 00:18:16,560
Don't tell me

194
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:19,879
it's because Mr. Narathon
is Mr. Phum's son

195
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,880
and now you don't trust him.

196
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:25,040
That's exactly the point.

197
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:30,119
But didn't you say
Mr. Narathon was a good man?

198
00:18:30,120 --> 00:18:33,760
That was before I knew he was Phum's son.

199
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:36,759
Have you ever heard the saying,

200
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:39,080
"The apple
doesn't fall far from the tree"?

201
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:45,160
Aren't you being too biased
against Mr. Phum?

202
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:48,479
I will never let businessmen like Phum

203
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:50,999
exploit nature for profit

204
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:53,640
on land that belongs to me.

205
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:02,160
Everything looks delicious.

206
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,160
You're more generous than I thought.

207
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:13,280
So stop dragging this out.

208
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,840
Tell me now.

209
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,359
You expect me to just sit here
and stare at the food?

210
00:19:21,360 --> 00:19:24,120
Eat while you tell me.

211
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,640
But seafood has to be peeled and cracked.

212
00:19:33,760 --> 00:19:36,519
And the curse of Skull Island

213
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:38,440
is rather complicated.

214
00:19:38,960 --> 00:19:41,760
I need to concentrate so I don't

215
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:44,280
miss any important parts.

216
00:19:46,520 --> 00:19:49,800
Don't tell me
I have to peel everything for you too.

217
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:52,920
That would be ideal.

218
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:58,400
But it's alright.

219
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:00,519
I can peel it myself.

220
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:02,239
Okay, okay.

221
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:05,360
I'll peel it for you.

222
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:10,959
Well, I changed my mind.

223
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,560
I want to eat the crab first.

224
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,440
Start talking.

225
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:24,520
You know I want to know it.

226
00:20:25,120 --> 00:20:27,040
Stop being so dramatic.

227
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:31,479
Once upon a time...

228
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:34,880
Hey, I'm not here for a fairy tale.

229
00:20:36,800 --> 00:20:37,920
Alright.

230
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:43,319
Well,

231
00:20:43,320 --> 00:20:46,440
the reason people believe
Skull Island is cursed

232
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,600
is because

233
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:50,920
most people who go near that area

234
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:53,320
either die

235
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:56,880
or disappear without a trace.

236
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:40,080
What were you doing?

237
00:23:40,880 --> 00:23:42,199
I've been knocking for ages.

238
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:45,400
I was in a warm bath and fell asleep.
That's why I didn't hear you.

239
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:47,280
Is that all?

240
00:23:49,120 --> 00:23:50,640
What did you think I was doing?

241
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:59,240
You thought I was hiding someone
in the bathroom?

242
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,159
No.

243
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:05,960
Why didn't you tell me
you were coming here?

244
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:09,200
Even without telling you,
you still managed to find me.

245
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:10,800
Mr. Phum.

246
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,320
Are you really going to ignore me?

247
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:19,000
I drove all this way.

248
00:24:20,040 --> 00:24:21,360
Did I ask you to come?

249
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:26,800
Since you're already here,
make yourself at home. I'll get changed.

250
00:24:27,400 --> 00:24:28,520
Mr. Phum.

251
00:24:45,080 --> 00:24:46,279
Hey.

252
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:48,480
Are you sure you're peeling this
for me willingly?

253
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,319
Why?

254
00:24:50,320 --> 00:24:51,480
Oh.

255
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:54,200
Look at it.

256
00:24:54,720 --> 00:24:56,720
This crab was so big,

257
00:24:57,240 --> 00:24:58,720
and you peeled it down to this size.

258
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:01,680
Where did all the meat go?

259
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:05,200
Well, I've never peeled crab
for anyone before.

260
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:08,199
You're lucky enough

261
00:25:08,200 --> 00:25:09,840
to eat the crab I peeled for you.

262
00:25:10,720 --> 00:25:13,120
Stop complaining and just eat it.

263
00:25:15,640 --> 00:25:16,839
Ow!

264
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:18,200
See?

265
00:25:19,320 --> 00:25:20,560
I knew this would happen.

266
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:22,999
What are you doing?

267
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,319
- I'll squeeze the blood out.
- That hurts.

268
00:25:25,320 --> 00:25:26,680
Then stay still.

269
00:25:28,160 --> 00:25:30,640
I'll squeeze the blood out. It's dirty.

270
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,280
This will hurt a bit.

271
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:59,640
Alright. Done.

272
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:04,360
You don't have to peel anymore.
I'll do it myself.

273
00:26:05,160 --> 00:26:06,800
You should've said you didn't know how.

274
00:26:08,440 --> 00:26:11,240
Then I won't get to hear the rest, will I?

275
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:14,719
It was just getting interesting.
You'll take forever to finish peeling.

276
00:26:14,720 --> 00:26:18,079
It's fine. I can peel

277
00:26:18,080 --> 00:26:19,480
and talk at the same time.

278
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:23,280
Where was I?

279
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:26,759
I asked you

280
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:28,639
whether the people
who went to Skull Island

281
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:30,879
didn't know about the curse.

282
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:31,840
They knew.

283
00:26:33,240 --> 00:26:34,960
Then why did they still go?

284
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,919
Because there was
something motivating them.

285
00:26:38,920 --> 00:26:40,840
That's why they still go.

286
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:44,360
Motivation? What is it?

287
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,600
Black Coral.

288
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,800
Black Coral?

289
00:27:29,800 --> 00:27:31,080
Oh, Kang.

290
00:27:31,840 --> 00:27:34,000
Mr. Phum, hello.

291
00:27:34,520 --> 00:27:36,280
I thought I was seeing things.

292
00:27:36,800 --> 00:27:37,920
Why?

293
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:41,120
I thought you had gone back to Bangkok.

294
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:44,399
I still have some business here.

295
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,639
Where are you going?

296
00:27:45,640 --> 00:27:47,520
I'm taking food to Uncle.

297
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,359
You have an uncle?

298
00:27:49,360 --> 00:27:51,440
He's not really my uncle.

299
00:27:52,160 --> 00:27:54,199
Uncle Pong isn't right in the head,

300
00:27:54,200 --> 00:27:55,720
and no one takes care of him.

301
00:27:56,320 --> 00:27:58,839
He usually eats at the temple,

302
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:01,359
but for the past few days,
he's been terrified of something

303
00:28:01,360 --> 00:28:04,400
and hiding in his shack.
So I have to bring food to him.

304
00:28:07,600 --> 00:28:09,440
You really are a good kid.

305
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,720
Then I'll go now. Goodbye.

306
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,320
Kang.

307
00:28:16,880 --> 00:28:17,840
Kang.

308
00:28:23,440 --> 00:28:25,960
Uncle, I brought you food.

309
00:28:29,400 --> 00:28:31,720
Uncle, I brought you food.

310
00:28:33,880 --> 00:28:35,720
Oh? Where did he go?

311
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:47,920
Uncle.

312
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:02,999
Uncle.

313
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,640
I brought you food.

314
00:29:07,160 --> 00:29:08,440
Don't be scared.

315
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:10,600
I brought you food.

316
00:29:24,760 --> 00:29:26,279
I'm not scared of you anymore.

317
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:28,479
You damn ghost! Die!

318
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:31,959
Uncle! Uncle! It's me!

319
00:29:31,960 --> 00:29:33,880
Uncle, it's me!

320
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:44,799
Kang, how are you?

321
00:29:44,800 --> 00:29:46,280
Are you alright?

322
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:49,000
Are you alright?

323
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:52,599
Hey.

324
00:29:52,600 --> 00:29:55,680
Don't go to that shack again.
It's dangerous.

325
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:57,799
He's never

326
00:29:57,800 --> 00:30:00,599
gone wild and hurt anyone before.

327
00:30:00,600 --> 00:30:03,560
You can't trust a madman.
One moment he's fine, the next he's not.

328
00:30:05,120 --> 00:30:08,080
Thank you so much for saving me.

329
00:30:09,760 --> 00:30:12,840
Why did you follow me there?

330
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:17,119
I was going to ask
if Narathon was at home.

331
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:20,760
But you ran off, so I followed you.

332
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:25,079
I don't know. I haven't been
to Thon's house today.

333
00:30:25,080 --> 00:30:29,040
I planned to bring food to Uncle first,
then go feed the fish.

334
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:33,959
Then why don't we go together?

335
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:36,040
That'd be good.

336
00:30:47,280 --> 00:30:50,320
Thank you for the meal.

337
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:54,520
No problem.

338
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:57,640
It was more than worth it
for the story you told me.

339
00:30:59,360 --> 00:31:01,080
Black Coral...

340
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:04,440
the precious jewel of the sea.

341
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,640
Don't take it too seriously.

342
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:12,240
It's just a story passed down
from person to person.

343
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:16,440
No one has ever actually seen
that so-called Black Coral.

344
00:31:41,560 --> 00:31:43,000
What are you thinking about?

345
00:31:46,280 --> 00:31:47,840
I'm just thinking I should head back

346
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:50,080
so you can go inside.

347
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:53,999
Okay. Excuse me then.

348
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:55,000
Okay.

349
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:17,880
How's it going, Kang? You're working hard.

350
00:32:18,680 --> 00:32:21,160
I told you,
you don't have to mop the house every day.

351
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:29,159
Mr. Phum has been waiting
for you for a long time.

352
00:32:29,160 --> 00:32:30,879
Kang, can you make me some coffee?

353
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:34,080
Of course.
I already plugged in the kettle.

354
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:41,960
Would you like some coffee too, Mr. Phum?

355
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,240
That would be nice.

356
00:32:49,240 --> 00:32:50,400
What do you want from me now?

357
00:32:51,520 --> 00:32:53,719
I'd like to stay here tonight.

358
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:55,520
You don't mind, do you?

359
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,280
Sure.

360
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:03,760
I was planning to go back
to Bangkok anyway.

361
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:07,800
You can sit or sleep wherever you want.

362
00:33:09,080 --> 00:33:10,360
I'll go pack.

363
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:25,800
Coffee's ready.

364
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:44,320
Your coffee's ready, Thon.

365
00:33:45,920 --> 00:33:48,319
Where did Mr. Phum go?

366
00:33:48,320 --> 00:33:50,400
Did he leave already?

367
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:52,399
I guess so.

368
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:54,960
What a shame.
He shouldn't have left so quickly.

369
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:56,759
Why?

370
00:33:56,760 --> 00:33:59,360
He's really fun to talk to.

371
00:34:00,320 --> 00:34:01,479
What did you talk about?

372
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,960
About you.

373
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:07,160
From when you were little until now.

374
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:09,678
He remembers everything.

375
00:34:09,679 --> 00:34:13,560
You're so lucky to have a father like him.

376
00:34:46,120 --> 00:34:47,440
Is the power out?

377
00:34:50,480 --> 00:34:52,638
The lights were fine

378
00:34:52,639 --> 00:34:54,600
when I came up in the elevator.

379
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,480
Happy birthday, Da.

380
00:36:06,040 --> 00:36:06,880
Na!

381
00:36:07,800 --> 00:36:10,679
You scared me to death.
I thought it was that ghost again.

382
00:36:10,680 --> 00:36:13,680
Don't ever surprise me like this again.
I don't like it.

383
00:36:14,200 --> 00:36:15,720
Wait, Da, I'm sorry.

384
00:36:16,360 --> 00:36:18,600
Da, Da.

385
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,720
Da, Da.

386
00:36:31,640 --> 00:36:34,120
Da. Da.

387
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:36,000
Da, I'm sorry.

388
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:41,400
Da, please open the door.

389
00:36:41,920 --> 00:36:43,320
Da.

390
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:57,240
Why did he stop?

391
00:36:57,760 --> 00:37:00,080
After scaring me like that,
why isn't he trying to make up with me?

392
00:37:09,440 --> 00:37:12,040
Seriously?

393
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:14,560
Don't tell me he left.

394
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:22,600
Na, what are you joking about?

395
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,360
Dara, listen carefully.

396
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:31,359
No. I'm not listening.

397
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:34,399
I'm mad at you. Get out.

398
00:37:34,400 --> 00:37:36,080
I said listen!

399
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,760
I need your help.

400
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,480
No...

401
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:47,720
No.

402
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:52,360
You are the only one who can help me.

403
00:37:53,040 --> 00:37:55,319
No! Stay away from me.

404
00:37:55,320 --> 00:37:57,840
I can't contact anyone except you.

405
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:00,679
Go be reborn already!

406
00:38:00,680 --> 00:38:03,800
Why are you haunting me?

407
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:06,800
You heartless woman.

408
00:38:30,000 --> 00:38:30,960
Da.

409
00:38:32,120 --> 00:38:33,760
You're not mad at me anymore, right?

410
00:38:38,760 --> 00:38:39,920
Da.

411
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:01,880
Sairung?

412
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:10,280
Hard to believe someone like her
would give up and leave that easily.

413
00:39:16,880 --> 00:39:18,000
Make sure you get it.

414
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:19,720
Hurry.

415
00:39:36,320 --> 00:39:38,679
Whoa.

416
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:41,640
You've got such a beautiful girlfriend
and didn't even introduce her?

417
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:45,039
Whoa, she's really beautiful.

418
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,160
Piak!

419
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:48,279
Were you eavesdropping on me?

420
00:39:48,280 --> 00:39:51,639
No. I was too far away to hear anything.

421
00:39:51,640 --> 00:39:54,359
I wasn't eavesdropping.
I was just watching.

422
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:56,920
Your girlfriend is gorgeous,
like an angel.

423
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:59,199
- She's not my girlfriend.
- Oh?

424
00:39:59,200 --> 00:40:02,000
Then why did she come to see you?

425
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:06,160
She's my old boss. She has a job for me.

426
00:40:08,240 --> 00:40:09,160
Go to bed now.

427
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:11,199
We start early tomorrow.

428
00:40:11,200 --> 00:40:13,040
What kind of job?

429
00:40:14,240 --> 00:40:15,840
Don't ask. Just go to bed.

430
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:19,000
Why so grumpy?

431
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:04,280
It's here.

432
00:41:06,040 --> 00:41:08,000
It's here.

433
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:11,159
You madman!

434
00:41:11,160 --> 00:41:13,960
You scared me. Go away!

435
00:41:14,720 --> 00:41:16,200
It's here.

436
00:41:17,400 --> 00:41:18,760
It's here.

437
00:41:21,440 --> 00:41:23,600
It's here.

438
00:41:28,560 --> 00:41:29,800
Sompong?

439
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:31,880
Is that you?

440
00:41:33,160 --> 00:41:34,320
You...

441
00:41:37,760 --> 00:41:40,759
Look ahead. Look ahead!

442
00:41:40,760 --> 00:41:44,440
Don't turn around. Don't turn around.
The moment you turn around, you die.

443
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:46,160
If you turn around, you die.

444
00:41:47,240 --> 00:41:48,840
No. Don't.

445
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,520
Whose voice is that?

446
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:53,080
Does Aunt Bua have stomach pain again?

447
00:43:44,640 --> 00:43:45,680
Kang.

448
00:43:46,840 --> 00:43:48,440
It's late. Why aren't you asleep?

449
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:51,319
Well,

450
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:53,360
I heard a woman crying.

451
00:43:54,360 --> 00:43:56,000
I thought it was Aunt Bua.

452
00:43:57,080 --> 00:43:59,360
She said her stomach hurt
earlier this evening.

453
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,840
Bua is fine now.

454
00:44:05,480 --> 00:44:07,720
She was just sitting
beside the pavilion earlier.

455
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:10,880
You must be hearing things.

456
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:13,560
Go to bed.

457
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:15,720
Alright.

458
00:44:19,400 --> 00:44:21,720
Remember this.

459
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:24,920
If you hear anything late at night,

460
00:44:25,840 --> 00:44:28,399
do not answer it.

461
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:29,840
Do not leave your room again.

462
00:44:32,200 --> 00:44:33,400
Okay.

463
00:44:36,960 --> 00:44:39,039
Hey, go.

464
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:40,920
Okay.

465
00:45:06,520 --> 00:45:08,400
It hurts.

466
00:45:09,920 --> 00:45:12,040
Help me.

467
00:45:17,880 --> 00:45:21,359
Don't tell me you're going diving
at Skull Island too.

468
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:23,320
You two are going to Skull Island?

469
00:45:30,080 --> 00:45:33,680
What if I told you
I saw the Black Coral that day?

470
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:35,120
Would you believe me?

471
00:45:36,000 --> 00:45:37,599
I might lose control

472
00:45:37,600 --> 00:45:39,840
and do something you'd never expect.

473
00:46:27,400 --> 00:46:29,880
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
